parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the engine stalls or shuts off while driving
the vehicle loses power
and the engine may hesitate or stumble.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident. It can also cause damage to other engine components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine overheats
coolant leaks
the check engine light illuminates
the engine loses power
and the vehicle may stall or shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil dipstick can cause the engine to overheat or seize, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The oil dipstick breaks off
making it impossible to check the oil level
and the engine may overheat or seize.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause gasoline to spill on the ground, leading to a fire hazard, and may also cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Gasoline spills on the ground when filling the tank
fuel pump sucks fuel back into the tank
unable to fill the tank at a normal pace
gas shoots back out of the tank
strong smell of gasoline inside the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine overheats
engine blown
service engine light comes on
engine has a sudden loss of power
engine has a delayed start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's systems to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Service engine light comes on
throttle pedal has no effect
vehicle will not accelerate
keyless entry system malfunction
windows will not roll down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities
or airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled airbags can lead to continued risk of injury or fatality due to faulty airbags, compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Recalled airbags are not repaired in a timely manner
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, compromising the safety of the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal fails to engage
or thumping sound/vibration is heard when pressing the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
indicating a potential problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or shut off without warning, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the vehicle loses power
the engine misfires
the check engine light is illuminated
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause engine overheating, coolant loss, and engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of power and control.
symptoms: The engine overheats
coolant is lost
the engine misfires
the check engine light is illuminated
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall or shut off without warning, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the vehicle loses power
the fuel pump loses pressure
and the check engine light is illuminated.
